			<section id='seekers'>
				<div class="large-10 small-12 large-centered columns">
					<h3>For Job Seekers</h3>
					<p>
						Interviews with students revealed that sometimes landing a job requires reaching out to a brother's ex-roommate or a mentor's other mentee. Sociologist Mark Granovetter's research also asserts that second and third degree, <a href='https://sociology.stanford.edu/sites/default/files/publications/the_strength_of_weak_ties_and_exch_w-gans.pdf'>less direct relationships are most effective</a>. In fact, many of the students we talked to were cognizant of this fact. Unfortunately, there's no way to discover distant, but efficacious relationships without manually crawling through contact lists or relying on luck. SixDegree aimed to weight and relationps to help people find distant degree connections with a strong relationship path.
					</p>
					<blockquote>
						I know people who know people in journalism, but I don't know which of them to ask for help.
					<footer>-Stanford Student</footer>
					</blockquote>
						

